# Aqala Project Structure

## Monorepo Layout

This repo contains two separate applications in different folders:

| Folder | Stack | Purpose |
|--------|-------|---------|
| `website/` | Next.js 16 | Web app — Vercel deployment |
| `aqala-mobile/` | Expo React Native | Mobile app — EAS Build (iOS/Android) |

## Key Rules

- **Never mix website and mobile code.** Each app has its own `package.json`, `node_modules`, and tooling.
- **website/** — Next.js App Router (`src/app/`), deployed to Vercel
- **aqala-mobile/** — Expo Router (`app/`), built with EAS for App Store / Play Store

## Shared at Root

- `.env` — copy to `website/.env` or `website/.env.local` for local web dev
- `firebase.json`, `firestore.rules` — Firebase config shared by both apps

## Deployment

- **Vercel:** Set Root Directory to `website`. Do not use repo root or `aqala-mobile`.
- **Website build:** Uses `next build --webpack` (Turbopack disabled for production build).
- **Mobile:** Use EAS Build from `aqala-mobile/` directory.
